Former Deputy Minority Whip of the House of Representatives and Managing Director, FBB Rice Milling Limited, Hon. Fatima Binta Bello has hailed the emergence of Governor Bala Mohammed of Bauchi state and Siminalayi Fubara of Rivers state as Chairman and Deputy of PDP Governors’ Forum. In a congratulatory message, Binta who represented the Katungo/Shongom federal constituency of Gombe state, described the election of the duo as a renewed hope for the opposition Peoples Democratic Party She said the election of Governor Bala and his Rivers state counterpart, Governor Fubara as Chairman and Deputy of the PDP Governors’ Forum is a good development that happened to the Party in recent time According to her, ‘They’re passionate and committed members of the Party and founded on their experience, they’ll provide a purposeful leadership to the Forum and renew hope for the Party”. It could be recalled that the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) had elected Bauchi State Governor, Sen. Bala Mohammed as Chairman of its Governors’ Forum, while Rivers State Governor, Siminalayi Fubara was elected as Deputy Chairman of the Forum. The election was held at the Bauchi state Government house last Saturday during the Party’s retreat conducted for its newly elected officials. Governor Bala Mohammed won his second term in the 2023 elections while Fubara was elected after the expiration of the second tenure of Governor Nyesom Wike.